a_n =\int^{\pi}_0 \frac{\sin(2n-1)x}{\sin x}dx
a_1,a_2,.....a_n
\pi
a_1 =a_2=a_3 =.....\pi
x\mapsto \dfrac x 2
a_n =\frac 1 2\int^{\pi/2}_0 \frac{\sin\left(n-\frac 12\right)x}{\sin \dfrac x2}dx
a_{n+1} =\frac 1 2\int^{\pi/2}_0 \frac{\sin\left(n+\frac 12\right)x}{\sin \dfrac x2}dx
\frac{\sin\left(n+\frac 12\right)x}{\sin \dfrac x2}= 1+2\sum_{k=1}^{n}\cos kx
